Class BaseSettingsStore

BaseResourceSettingsStore, MemorySettingsStore
public abstract class BaseSettingsStore extends BaseRepeater implements SettingsStore, RegistryTrait, JavaTrait
Service Provider API

Base class for SettingsStore provider implementations.

Provided Stores

  • Deployment - Loads settings for a particular application or server deployment
  • ResourceFolderSettingsStore - Loads settings from .properties files
  • MemorySettingsStore - A store of non-persistent settings objects in memory

Deployments are the most commonly used settings store and typically they should be all that is required by most applications. See Deployment for detailed usage examples.

Providers

SettingsStore providers inherit several useful methods and implementations from this base class:

  • index(SettingsObject) - Adds the given object to the store's in-memory index (but not to any persistent storage)
  • indexed() - The set of objects in this store. If the store is loadable, load() is called before returning the set
  • unload() - Clears this store's in-memory index
  • iterator() - Iterates through each settings Object in this store
  • load() - Lazy-loads objects from persistent storage by calling onLoad() and then adds them to the in-memory index
  • lookup(SettingsObject.Identifier) - Looks up the object for the given identifier in the store's index
  • save(SettingsObject) - Saves the given settings object to persistent storage by calling onSave(SettingsObject)

Providers must override these methods (although some may be unsupported methods):

  • SettingsStore.accessModes() - Specifies the kinds of access that the store supports
  • onLoad() - Loads settings objects from persistent storage
  • onSave(SettingsObject) - Saves the settings object to persistent storage
  • onDelete(SettingsObject) = Deleted the given settings object from persistent storage
  • onUnload() - Unloads all settings from this store (but does not remove them from persistent storage)
